    </section>


    <!-- Montjuic Castle Dropdown -->
    <section class="destination-section">
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Montjuic Castle</h2>
        <p>Near the Joan Miro Foundation is the <strong>Teleferic de Montjuic</strong>, an aerial tramway which takes you to the top of the hill where the Montjuic Castle is located. The aerial tram ride provides amazing views over Barcelona and is a much easier option than hiking the short but steep path to the top of the hill.</p>
        <p>The <strong>Montjuic Castle</strong> is a large 17th century fortress which later served as a prison. Today the fortress hosts a military museum and offers incredible views over the coast, as well as part of the city.</p>
        <!-- Read More Read Less Tab -->
        <div class="hidden-content" class="destination-section">
            <h3>Barcelona Olympic Park</h3>
            <p>Atop Montjuic you'll also find the expansive Olympic Park, which includes a giant stadium as well as many other sports complexes. The Olympic Park was constructed for the Barcelona Olympics in 1992.</p>
        </div>
